{"ID": 55466, "name": "United States v. Ressam", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/cases/2007/07-455", "view_count": 0, "docket_number": "07-455", "timeline": [{"event": "Granted", "dates": [1197007200], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/39901"}, {"event": "Argued", "dates": [1206421200], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/39902"}, {"event": "Decided", "dates": [1211173200], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/39903"}], "question": "<p>Does 18 U.S.C. Section 844(h)(2), which prohibits carrying explosives \"during the commission of any felony\", apply to a defendant convicted of lying to a customs agent because the explosives were not carried \"in relation to\" the underlying felony?</p>\n", "citation": {"volume": "553", "page": "272", "year": "2008", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_citation/case_citation/20769"}, "term": "2007", "description": null, "justia_url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/553/272/"}